Their only goal is to make money to support families left at home.
From December 1, the law came into force, according to which every migrant worker will be obliged to pass an exam for knowledge of the Russian language.
So far, this rule applies only to those who intend to work in the service, housing and communal services, household and retail trade.
However, over time, - promise in the FMS, - tests will become mandatory for all visitors.
Moreover, you will have to pass not only the language, but also Russian history, and the basics of legislation.
Knowledge of the language will have to be confirmed for obtaining and for renewing a work permit.
The exception applies only to citizens of those countries where Russian is the state language.
People who managed to obtain certificates and diplomas of education before the collapse of the USSR in 1991 are not covered by the law.
Benefits, doom and protection of rights
The network of examination points will work under the auspices of the Pushkin Institute of the Russian Language, the Peoples' Friendship University, Moscow State University, St. Petersburg State University and other Russian universities.
Migrants will be able to pass tests in all cities; already now more than 160 such centers have been opened in Russia.
The initiative to introduce testing was supported by both deputies of the State Duma and the FMS.
