It's just a conventional name, just like my friends in Boston call themselves Irish, and friends from New York consider themselves Italian.
Later, I settled on a complex design of “American of Mexican origin”.
But I was here in Mexico.
Here, in the homeland of my grandfather, there was no need for conditional names or complex designs.
I was just an American.
