For Mexico, relations with the United States are a difficult and fulfilling old grievances.
Most Americans never thought about the fact that in 1848 the United States invaded Mexico and at gunpoint forced its leaders to abandon half of its territory.
But Mexicans think for centuries, not minutes, and see reminders of those events in everything.
Therefore, it is only necessary for any US statesman to say at least a word of criticism towards Mexico, in the press and among the elite of Mexican society, there are immediately complaints that the Americans encroach on the sovereignty of its neighbors.
And the descendants of Montezuma are filled with belligerence.
At the same time, the most difficult is the relationship between Mexico and more than 35 million Mexican-Americans living in the United States.
Do you want to talk about offenses?
They're enough.
In Mexico, there are winners and losers, people who find opportunities for themselves in this country, and those for whom there are no such opportunities.
In Los Angeles, Las Vegas, Phoenix, Denver or San Antonio, there are so many people of Mexican origin for only one reason: at some point in their family history, someone - a father or grandfather - had no opportunity to realize himself in Mexico and was forced to go north.
Most often, it was Mexicans of a certain type - swarthy, poorly educated, from poor peasant families.
We are their descendants, and we remember that.
In Mexico, it is seen differently.
Today, our life is the embodiment of the American dream, we studied in good schools and got a job for good work, but we will not forget that even this dream is American, not Mexican.
Our national self-determination is confusing and unclear, but we know which country to consider its own.
United States of America.
