We don’t speak Spanish well enough, and our ties with Mexico are not strong enough.
Our very existence is explained by failures.
If our ancestors had succeeded in Mexico, they wouldn't have left.
We would not be behind the Silk Curtain, finding a well-fed life in the United States, but having lost spiritual connections.
My wife was born in Guadalajara and legally moved to the United States as a child, and this reminds me that there are certain frictions between real Mexicans and Americans of Mexican descent - Mexicans are more clear about their national identity, and Americans of Mexican origin are offended.
