At the same time, many of my familiar Americans of Mexican origin do not feel belonging to any of them.
We listen to the Mexican band Los Tigres del Norte, but we love Bruce Springsteen.
Getting the best of two worlds, you inevitably lose roots.
We are Americans in Mexico.
In the United States, we are called Mexicans.
