“People are very overstrained, housing is expensive, as well as education, and because of this, many people are putting it off,” says the young manager.
Other people may have children.
“But it’s important for me to have my own money and time,” says another young man for 20 years.
Men and women mention their careers, stress and housing prices and education as the reasons that prevent them from having children.
So, no matter how the government tries to encourage its citizens to have children, the last word rests with Singapore.
Personal in offline - personal online
Confidentiality.
According to the dictionary of the Royal Academy of Spanish, we are talking about the property of a private or “sphere of privacy that have the right to protect against any interference.”
What is personal for a minor under the age of 16?
How does he apply this definition in his daily life and social media?
Does he understand the dangers he is exposed to when discussing on the Internet situations that he probably wouldn’t share outside the Internet?
elPeriódio interviewed five children from ten to 15 years old, frequent users of the network.
In four cases, they associated the term with “something very mine”, in the personal plane, and “password and username” when applied to social networks.
“I wouldn’t upload my biggest secrets,” says ten-year-old Jorge when trying to explain the meaning of personal sites like Facebook, Twitter, Hotmail, and Windows Live Messenger, where he has accounts for two years.
